The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Blast arrest 

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Chandigarh, Sept. 9: Police today arrested a man who is suspected to have planted a pipe bomb at the Sector 17 interstate bus stand here last night. Seven persons were injured in the blast.

 The arrest was made from the Sector 43 bus stand. Charanjit Singh alias Channi has links with the Khalistan Commando Force based in Pakistan. Two pipe bombs and 500 grams of explosive were recovered from him, said inspector-general of police Satish Chandra.

 Charanjit was caught on the Indo-Pak border in 1990 and was lodged in Jammu jail till his release two months ago. 




